      "set:html": "<hr>\n<div class=\"sl-heading-wrapper level-h2\"><h2 id=\"14-self-check\">14. Self-Check</h2><a class=\"sl-anchor-link\" href=\"#14-self-check\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"sl-anchor-icon\"><svg width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"currentcolor\" d=\"m12.11 15.39-3.88 3.88a2.52 2.52 0 0 1-3.5 0 2.47 2.47 0 0 1 0-3.5l3.88-3.88a1 1 0 0 0-1.42-1.42l-3.88 3.89a4.48 4.48 0 0 0 6.33 6.33l3.89-3.88a1 1 0 1 0-1.42-1.42Zm8.58-12.08a4.49 4.49 0 0 0-6.33 0l-3.89 3.88a1 1 0 0 0 1.42 1.42l3.88-3.88a2.52 2.52 0 0 1 3.5 0 2.47 2.47 0 0 1 0 3.5l-3.88 3.88a1 1 0 1 0 1.42 1.42l3.88-3.89a4.49 4.49 0 0 0 0-6.33ZM8.83 15.17a1 1 0 0 0 1.1.22 1 1 0 0 0 .32-.22l4.92-4.92a1 1 0 0 0-1.42-1.42l-4.92 4.92a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.42Z\"></path></svg></span><span class=\"sr-only\">Section titled “14. Self-Check”</span></a></div>\n<p>Before you start Lab 1, make sure you can answer these questions <em>without looking them up</em>:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>What problem does preemption solve that your bare-metal loop cannot?</li>\n<li>A task calls <code dir=\"auto\">vTaskDelay(pdMS_TO_TICKS(50))</code>. What state does it enter? How much CPU does it use while waiting?</li>\n<li>You have a task at priority 3 and another at priority 1. The priority-3 task is Blocked on a queue. Which one runs? What happens the instant data arrives in the queue?</li>\n<li>What is <code dir=\"auto\">configTOTAL_HEAP_SIZE</code> and what happens if you set it too small?</li>\n<li>Why must you use <code dir=\"auto\">xQueueSendFromISR()</code> inside an interrupt handler instead of <code dir=\"auto\">xQueueSend()</code>?</li>\n<li>Your stopwatch has a timekeeping task and a display task. Which should have higher priority, and why?</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If you got stuck on any of these, re-read the relevant section above. These concepts will show up immediately in your lab work.</p>\n<hr>\n<div class=\"sl-heading-wrapper level-h2\"><h2 id=\"whats-next\">What’s Next</h2><a class=\"sl-anchor-link\" href=\"#whats-next\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"sl-anchor-icon\"><svg width=\"16\" height=\"16\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"currentcolor\" d=\"m12.11 15.39-3.88 3.88a2.52 2.52 0 0 1-3.5 0 2.47 2.47 0 0 1 0-3.5l3.88-3.88a1 1 0 0 0-1.42-1.42l-3.88 3.89a4.48 4.48 0 0 0 6.33 6.33l3.89-3.88a1 1 0 1 0-1.42-1.42Zm8.58-12.08a4.49 4.49 0 0 0-6.33 0l-3.89 3.88a1 1 0 0 0 1.42 1.42l3.88-3.88a2.52 2.52 0 0 1 3.5 0 2.47 2.47 0 0 1 0 3.5l-3.88 3.88a1 1 0 1 0 1.42 1.42l3.88-3.89a4.49 4.49 0 0 0 0-6.33ZM8.83 15.17a1 1 0 0 0 1.1.22 1 1 0 0 0 .32-.22l4.92-4.92a1 1 0 0 0-1.42-1.42l-4.92 4.92a1 1 0 0 0 0 1.42Z\"></path></svg></span><span class=\"sr-only\">Section titled “What’s Next”</span></a></div>\n<p>The guides below cover each FreeRTOS feature in depth. You’ll need them as you work through the labs:</p>\n"
